[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "Review verifies AWS SDK API correctness across all services used (dedicated 'AWS SDK Accuracy' section covering DynamoDB, Kinesis, Timestream, S3, EventBridge, CloudWatch, SageMaker Runtime, Feature Store Runtime, Bedrock Runtime, and boto3 Config). Identifies 14 real issues with explicit severity ratings (3 WARNINGs, 11 NOTEs), each with Severity/Location/Description fields. The three WARNINGs are technically accurate and high-impact: (1) DynamoDB's Limit-applied-before-FilterExpression behavior in on_canonical_event causes silent loss on re-enrolled patients; (2) missing LastEvaluatedKey pagination on GSI sweeps drops patients past the 1MB response cap; (3) within-sample standardization in compute_top_drivers is mathematically nonsensical because mean/std across mixed-scale features in a single observation has no statistical meaning. Each finding ships a concrete 'How to fix' code snippet showing the corrected pattern (composite GSI keyed on patient_id+is_active, pagination loop with ExclusiveStartKey, coef_*X partial-contribution proxy). Healthcare-specific concerns are addressed (PHI logging, LOINC anchoring, unit conversion, Decimal discipline at DynamoDB boundary, KMS encryption, BAA-eligible services, calibration discipline, FDA SaMD framing). Pseudocode-to-Python consistency table maps all eight steps. Re-review checklist gives a verifier a numbered list of items to confirm. Meets the pass condition fully."}